S1iQ0-JEkl.description: Enabled or not. If set to `false` pulses on `UPD` do not change the output value. Effectively that means the timer is paused. Set to `true` again to continue time counting.
S1iQ0-JEkl.label: EN

HylxTMkE1l.description: The current time value in seconds.

rkxxxaM141e.description: Resets the current time value to zero.
rkxxxaM141e.label: RST

SJQlg6zkVke.description: Enabled or not. If set to `false` pulses on `UPD` do not change the output value. Effectively that means the timer is paused. Set to `true` again to continue time counting.
SJQlg6zkVke.label: EN

H1lW3xXJEye.description: Reset. Cancels the current rotation. Neither `DONE` nor `ERR` will fire after a pulse on `RST`.
H1lW3xXJEye.label: RST

BJZbhlX14kx.description: Fires when the rotation is impossible. For example, if the value of `PPS` is wrong.
BJZbhlX14kx.label: ERR

S1fbnxQ1Eke.description: Pulses per second. Defines the rotation speed: number of steps a motor is expected to perform in one second. Should not be zero. The upper limit is defined by characteristics of the connected motor.
S1fbnxQ1Eke.label: PPS

Bkmbhx7yVke.description: A board port to which the step port of the driver is connected.
Bkmbhx7yVke.label: STEP

B1VZ2lXJNyx.description: Starts a new rotation which will make `N` steps at `PPS` rate.
B1VZ2lXJNyx.label: GO

SyU-nem1Eye.description: Number of steps to make. Many motors have 200 or 400 steps per revolution. Pass a negative value to rotate in the backward direction. Set to `+Inf` or `-Inf` to run an infinite rotation.
SyU-nem1Eye.label: N
